---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import CertificationsStrip from "../components/CertificationsStrip.astro";
import CTABand from "../components/CTABand.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Peregrine Systems"
  description="Peregrine Systems is a senior-led Salesforce practice for teams from small to enterprise. Built around two pillars: True Consulting and Usable Knowledge."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="About"
    title="A senior-led Salesforce practice."
    lede="We help teams from small to enterprise get more out of Salesforce — through consulting that challenges the brief, and documentation that makes the system legible to everyone who has to work with it."
  />

  {/* What we do — the two named pillars carry this section. */}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8">
      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.9fr)_minmax(0,1.1fr)] md:items-end">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">What we do</span>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl">Two pillars.</h2>
          <span class="rule-divider mt-6"></span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-muted)] md:max-w-prose">
          Most of what makes the work different sits in two ideas. One is about the conversation that
          should happen before you build. The other is about how the system gets understood once it's
          running.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-px overflow-hidden rounded border border-[color:var(--color-rule)] bg-[color:var(--color-rule)] sm:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8">
          <span class="font-[Fraunces,serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">01</span>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-2xl">True Consulting</h3>
          <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-2)]">
            <p>
              We push back before we build. The wrong ask, executed cleanly, is still the wrong outcome —
              so we challenge requirements at the start of every engagement and scope toward solutions
              that scale.
            </p>
            <p>
              The result is less rework, fewer reversals, and an org that holds up as the business grows
              into it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8">
          <span class="font-[Fraunces,serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">02</span>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-2xl">Usable Knowledge</h3>
          <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-2)]">
            <p>
              Standard documentation lives in silos — one place for the process, another for the
              automation. We deliver a single visual map of your business process with the underlying
              automation overlaid.
            </p>
            <p>
              Stakeholders see the whole picture and can make decisions on it. Developers know where new
              features intercept what's already there.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            href="/system-mapping"
            class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)] link-underline"
          >
            See System Mapping <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* How we do it — operating posture. */}
  <section class="section bg-[color:var(--color-cream-2)]">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="eyebrow">How we do it</span>
        <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl">How the work actually runs.</h2>
        <span class="rule-divider rule-divider-center mt-6"></span>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-14 grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="relative pl-6 border-l border-[color:var(--color-gold)]/60">
          <div class="font-[Fraunces,serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">01</div>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl leading-snug">Senior, not stretched.</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-muted)]">
            You work with the lead consultant. No layered staffing, no junior account team — just the
            person doing the work.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="relative pl-6 border-l border-[color:var(--color-gold)]/60">
          <div class="font-[Fraunces,serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">02</div>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl leading-snug">Configure before you code.</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-muted)]">
            We exhaust declarative tools before reaching for Apex. Your future admin will thank us.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="relative pl-6 border-l border-[color:var(--color-gold)]/60">
          <div class="font-[Fraunces,serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">03</div>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl leading-snug">Outcomes over hours.</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-muted)]">
            We scope to the result you need. You see exactly what you're getting and what it costs
            before we start.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Why we do it — mission, then wedge. */}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-5xl px-5 sm:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="eyebrow">Why we do it</span>
        <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl">Why Peregrine Systems.</h2>
        <span class="rule-divider rule-divider-center mt-6"></span>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-2xl space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-2)]">
        {/* TODO: Replace mission paragraph with client-approved wording (open input #2). */}
        <p>
          We started this firm to run Salesforce engagements the way the engagements we'd choose to
          be on actually run — senior consultants who own the work end-to-end, a clear-eyed
          conversation about what should actually be built, and a living map of the system so the
          people deciding what comes next can see it.
        </p>

        {/* Wedge-against-large-SIs block. Framed without naming competitors. */}
        <p>
          The rest of why is reaction. Large doesn't mean responsive — calls go unreturned and weeks
          slip. Generalist doesn't mean qualified for your specifics — the senior on the pitch is
          rarely the senior on your account, and rarely the one who's seen your problem before. We
          built Peregrine Systems for orgs that need the deep, specific consultant they were
          promised.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CertificationsStrip />
  <CTABand />
</BaseLayout>
